---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
import StudentCard from '@/components/StudentCard.astro'
---

<BaseLayout title="Our Team">
  <article class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 py-6 sm:py-12">
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-indigo-700 dark:text-indigo-400 mb-6">Research Scholars</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <StudentCard
          name="Kalyani Prashant Kolte"
          role="Research Scholar (Co-Supervised by Dr. Shyamanta M Hazarika)"
          startDate="Oct 2025"
          imageSrc="/kalyani.png"
          description={`"The unknown isn't a risk, it's an invitation" \n
                        Hi, I’m Kalyani, fascinated by how we can make machines think smarter with less crafting lightweight, memory- and hardware-efficient algorithms that do more with fewer bits, bytes, and watts.
                        Code feels like a playground to me where logic, math, and creativity collide, and something new always emerges from the chaos.
                        When I’m not chasing efficiency curves, you’ll probably find me chasing rebounds on the basketball court, because both research and basketball are about timing, precision, and not giving up after a few missed shots.`}
          email="k.kalyani@iitg.ac.in"
          compact={false}
          collapsible={true}
        />
        <StudentCard
          name="Gourish Majumdar"
          role="Research Scholar"
          startDate="Oct 2025"
          imageSrc="/Gourish.jpg"
          description={`Hi there! I’m Gourish Majumdar, currently exploring the fascinating world of deep learning — from physics-inspired models that
                        borrow wisdom from nature’s equations to questions of privacy and security in modern AI systems.
                        I come from a physics background, where you spend years chasing constants of nature — and now I’m in deep learning, where even the loss function can’t stay constant for five epochs.
                        Somewhere between conserved quantities and exploding gradients lies my comfort zone.
                        When I’m not pondering over gradients or loss functions, you’ll probably find me reading random science facts, watching movies, or getting lost in music. Still figuring things out — both in research and in life! `}
          email="m.gourish@iitg.ac.in"
          website="https://www.linkedin.com/in/gourish-majumdar-b378a6341/"
          compact={false}
          collapsible={true}
        />
        <StudentCard
          name="Vaishnavi Nagabhushana"
          role="Research Scholar"
          startDate="Aug 2024"
          imageSrc="/Vaishnavi.jpg"
          description={`Hey there! I’m Vaishnavi N , I explore the fascinating intersection of brains and machines — building systems that not only think but adapt.
                        My work focuses on neuro-inspired AI, computer vision, TinyML, and continual learning — shaping AI that evolves like we do.
                        When I'm not training machines to be a little more human, you’ll find me painting walls into stories or swimming my way through ideas.`}
          email="n.vaishnavi@iitg.ac.in"
          website="https://vaishnavin.pages.dev/"
          compact={false}
          collapsible={true}
        />

        <StudentCard
          name="Kartikay Agrawal"
          role="Research Scholar"
          startDate="Jan 2024"
          imageSrc="/Kartikay.png"
          description={`“Curiosity kills a cat, not a Research Scholar” \n
                        I am Kartikay, I like diving into understanding brain mechanisms and translating them into neuroscience-inspired, efficient ML algorithms.
                        After all, what’s an algorithm without math standing over it with a stick, demanding it confess its crimes?
                        When I’m not wrangling data or debugging code, you’ll probably find me in an amphitheatre or a stage (probably with my guitar).
                        Basically, I try to balance logic with a little bit of drama.`}
          email="a.kartikay@iitg.ac.in"
          website="https://www.linkedin.com/in/kartikayagrawal/"
          compact={false}
          collapsible={true}
        />
      </div>
    </section>

